Heya, I’m Tim. :wave: I’m from Europe, currently working as a Swift developer. I learned about Rust at the end of last year and quickly got very interested, its design goals really appeal to me.
I’ve been making some minor contributions to the Rust repo for a couple months now. I’m mostly interested in the collection types and the iterator APIs, so that’s what I’ll keep contributing to for the time being :slight_smile:
Looks like these topics aren’t really discussed here on Zulip?

Hey Tim; welcome to the Rust community!

Looks like these topics aren’t really discussed here on Zulip?

These are mostly library team matters and currently, the library team is not on Zulip but rather on IRC. As IRC is being sunsetted, I think the library team will move somewhere else soon.

Hey, if you need any code review, count me in
Welcome to the channel!
